@playXE note that slirp4netns doesn't support TCP window scaling (meaning that TCP windows are limited to 64 KiB), so the throughput will dramatically decrease as the RTT of the peer increases.

That probably doesn't explain the missing bytes, but if git happens to contact a server with 200ms RTT for you (you can quickly check with `ping` or `traceroute`) you should expect abysmal throughput. See also https://github.com/containers/podman/issues/17865#issuecomment-1477638812

Would you have a chance to try with [pasta](https://passt.top/passt/about/#pasta-pack-a-subtle-tap-abstraction) (`--net=pasta`) as network back-end for Podman? The AUR [package](https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/passt-git) is up to date, and given the setup you described I don't expect that you need to change anything else to use it.
